text: The rooms were clean and comfortable. Easy access to my daughter who was in ICU. I was able to walk to the elevator which were only a small walk away, this made my stay less stressful knowing that she was just up stairs. Thank you Princeton Guest Rooms.

name: Kyle Whitson
text: Rooms are so conveniently located in the hospital without ever stepping outside. But the price doesn't seem to fit what it seems they are for. A Baptist organization made on campus rooms for families from afar who need a place tobstart to be near their loved ones, but it's priced about $15 more than most hitks I ever stayed in that have pools spas bars restaurants live music free shuttle etc. I was not even able to get a loan Ethernet or HDMI cable to use for an hour or two. and the tv channels are limited so bring your roku.  it was a long walk every trip from room to my mom room but I'm glad I was able to go often . And if you get outside the fence there especially at night. Be prepared be ready be locked and loaded. But they worked with usbwhen we had to get several people to call and pat a portion of the daily rental fee. last thing . There is some one to answer the phone anytime  between about 8 am to 330 pm Monday thru Friday except weekends or holidays on them off days Just hope you don't run short of towels or worse toilet paper.
